  "texts": [
    "Trust, a cornerstone of any technology's acceptance and use, is paramount in the context of AI, where decisions made by a model can have significant implications for individuals and society [10,11,12].",
    "Ethical considerations, too, play a critical role, as the deployment of AI must adhere to principles that prevent harm, ensure fairness, and protect privacy [13,14].",
    "Furthermore, regulatory compliance emerges as a compelling motivator, with governments around the world beginning to enact laws that require AI systems to be transparent and their decisions explainable, and this regulatory landscape necessitates a concerted effort from researchers and developers to create models that are not only powerful and efficient but also accountable and comprehensible to their users [15,16,17,18].",
    "ObjectiveThe primary objective of this study is to evaluate the interpretability and explainability of several prominent LLMs: TripoSR by Stability AI, Gemma-7b by Google, Mistral 7B by Mistral AI, Llama-2-7b by Meta, and GemMoE-Beta-1 by CrystalCare AI.",
    "These models, representing the cutting edge of language processing capabilities, serve as benchmarks for assessing the current state of LLM transparency and understandability."
